WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:51.218 --> 00:53.912
So many people
settle for love that

00:53.913 --> 00:56.680
doesn't really ask
anything of them,

00:56.765 --> 00:59.428
that they don't have to
make any sacrifices for.

01:00.352 --> 01:01.638
I don't want that.

01:02.396 --> 01:05.855
I want an ideal love that I
have to give everything to.

01:56.408 --> 01:57.774
Where are you?

01:59.202 --> 02:00.818
Where are you?

02:06.585 --> 02:08.622
Why are you doing this?

02:27.606 --> 02:28.813
In the name of the Father...

02:33.987 --> 02:37.355
Benedicamus Domino

02:42.162 --> 02:45.655
Benedicamus Domino

02:45.749 --> 02:47.581
Dear Christ.

03:30.210 --> 03:33.248
I was 17 years old when
I came to the convent,

03:33.338 --> 03:35.546
18 when I entered the novitiate.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.533
I know a lot of people could
probably never understand...

04:10.375 --> 04:13.539
Never understand how
someone so young

04:13.628 --> 04:15.961
with their entire
life ahead of them

04:17.466 --> 04:19.673
would want to give
it all away to God.

04:26.141 --> 04:29.509
They think of nuns today, and
they see a bunch of old women.

04:29.603 --> 04:31.811
Women who couldn't find husbands,

04:31.897 --> 04:34.480
or for some reason,

04:34.566 --> 04:36.774
just couldn't make it
in the outside world.

04:45.202 --> 04:48.445
So they ran off to a monastery
to escape everything.

04:59.424 --> 05:03.338
What they don't understand is
that beneath everything else...

05:17.067 --> 05:18.899
We were women in love.

05:20.570 --> 05:22.527
You're all I could ever want.

05:53.854 --> 05:55.686
You ready for this?

05:55.772 --> 05:57.934
Okay, you can come
right out this way.

06:08.285 --> 06:09.617
Is my hair all right?

06:14.791 --> 06:16.248
Good morning, Father.

06:25.760 --> 06:29.253
Nora Harris? I can't
believe it. Is it you?

06:29.347 --> 06:31.304
Hey, Rob, it sure
is. How you been?

06:31.391 --> 06:34.054
I've been good. I've
been real good.

06:34.144 --> 06:38.013
Now, wait a minute. Now don't
tell me. Is this Cathleen?

06:38.690 --> 06:40.727
It sure is. Can you believe
it? Look how big she got.

06:40.817 --> 06:43.400
My goodness. Hey, pretty
lady. How are you?

06:43.486 --> 06:45.694
You know, you're not allowed
to grow up that fast.

06:47.157 --> 06:48.648
Soon, you'll be taller than me.

06:49.826 --> 06:52.159
I gotta say, Nora, I'm a little
surprised to see you here.

06:52.245 --> 06:53.577
I've known you all my life,

06:53.663 --> 06:55.347
and I don't think
I've ever seen you

06:55.348 --> 06:57.077
within 500 yards of
a Sunday service.

06:57.167 --> 06:59.079
Yeah, well, don't
get your hopes up.

06:59.169 --> 07:00.910
I'm not here to be saved
or nothing like that.

07:01.004 --> 07:02.165
I just thought it about time

07:02.255 --> 07:04.963
that Cathleen learned
what religion was about.

07:05.050 --> 07:07.081
Or supposed to be about, you know.

07:07.082 --> 07:08.082
Yeah.

07:08.083 --> 07:09.676
Plus, we were a little
bored, weren't we?

07:09.763 --> 07:12.255
Well, hey, that's all right with
me. I'm just glad you're here.

07:12.349 --> 07:13.816
- Let's get you all a good seat.
- All right.

07:13.892 --> 07:16.179
Come on in. Right there's
two, right up front there.

07:16.269 --> 07:18.181
Blessed be God the Father.

07:18.271 --> 07:22.436
Because although you have not
seen Him, you still love Him.

07:23.234 --> 07:26.352
Although you do not know Him,
you still believe in Him.

07:27.030 --> 07:30.740
You feel His presence all around
without knowing His name,

07:30.825 --> 07:35.069
and you rejoice with an
indescribable ecstasy.

07:36.206 --> 07:38.698
Because if there's
one thing we know,

07:38.792 --> 07:41.785
it's that God's love
is unconditional.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.373
Put your napkin in your lap.

07:48.802 --> 07:50.134
Thank you.

07:56.559 --> 07:58.642
Did you like going to
that church today?

07:58.728 --> 08:00.560
Yeah, I did.

08:00.647 --> 08:01.808
Yeah?

08:02.565 --> 08:04.522
What'd you like about it the most?

08:06.861 --> 08:08.102
I don't know.

08:08.196 --> 08:10.688
I guess I just thought
it was peaceful.

08:12.242 --> 08:13.858
"Peaceful," huh?

08:15.996 --> 08:18.204
Yeah, I guess it was
kind of peaceful.

08:18.289 --> 08:20.497
What kind of church was it, again?

08:21.209 --> 08:23.417
That was a Catholic church.

08:26.589 --> 08:27.921
Are we Catholic?

08:28.842 --> 08:30.174
No, we're not anything.

08:30.260 --> 08:32.798
I don't really believe
in religion, actually.

08:32.886 --> 08:35.220
I think it's kind
of a waste of time.

08:35.974 --> 08:40.684
But when you're older, you
can decide for yourself.

08:51.573 --> 08:53.530
Looks like Daddy's home.

09:03.835 --> 09:06.373
Hey, hey, hey, baby.

09:07.172 --> 09:09.664
How's Daddy's little girl?

09:10.717 --> 09:12.925
What'd you do today? Did
you have a good day today?

09:13.011 --> 09:14.127
Daddy, where were you?

09:14.220 --> 09:15.802
We've been waiting
for you for so long.

09:15.889 --> 09:18.472
Yeah, it's a valid question,
Chuck. Where you been?

09:18.558 --> 09:20.140
I was out. That's all.

09:20.226 --> 09:24.937
Okay. Because we've been sitting
here all day, waiting on you.

09:25.023 --> 09:26.639
You never heard of a phone or...

09:26.733 --> 09:29.146
Come on, Nora, please. Of
course I've heard of a phone.

09:29.235 --> 09:32.353
Well, that's good. You've heard
of a phone. That's nice.

09:33.615 --> 09:34.947
What do you want me to say, Nora?

09:35.200 --> 09:38.364
Is there anything in particular
that you'd like to hear me say?

09:38.453 --> 09:39.489
I don't know, Chuck.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.010
Maybe I'd just like
you to be a man

09:41.011 --> 09:42.322
every once in a while, you know?

09:42.415 --> 09:44.156
Be a fucking father for a change,

09:44.250 --> 09:46.207
maybe learn to sacrifice
a little bit.

09:46.294 --> 09:49.628
Give me a break, okay? Are
you serious with that?

09:49.714 --> 09:52.297
What, you want me to drop it,
Chuck? Is that what you want?

09:52.383 --> 09:53.624
- Yeah.
- Well, fuck you.

09:53.718 --> 09:56.802
Fuck me? Fuck you, Nora.

09:56.888 --> 09:59.301
As a matter of fact,
fuck all this shit.

09:59.390 --> 10:00.471
I'm sick of this.

10:00.558 --> 10:03.175
I'm sorry that I can't be the
person you want me to be.

10:03.269 --> 10:05.135
No, you can't be the man
I wanted you to be.

10:05.230 --> 10:07.062
- You are the opposite of that.
- Okay. All right.

10:07.148 --> 10:10.607
I was out. That's all. You
can't handle that, I'm gone.

10:10.693 --> 10:11.993
Where do you think
you're going, Chuck?

10:12.070 --> 10:13.070
You're not leaving.

10:13.154 --> 10:15.396
You got a little
girl now. Hear me?

10:15.490 --> 10:18.528
- If you leave, you get out.
- Well, fuck you.

10:27.919 --> 10:29.831
Honey, will you take this for me?

10:30.880 --> 10:32.041
You got it?

10:36.136 --> 10:37.752
Excuse me?

10:37.846 --> 10:39.678
Can I help you?

10:39.764 --> 10:41.596
Yes. Are you Mrs Harris?

10:42.225 --> 10:44.558
- Yes.
- My name is Sister Gloria.

10:44.644 --> 10:46.431
This is Sister Eleanor.

10:46.521 --> 10:48.513
We're from Our Lady
of Blessed Sorrows,

10:48.606 --> 10:50.939
the parochial school
just up the road.

10:51.901 --> 10:57.067
We are very proud to say that it
is the nuns, Sisters like us,

10:57.157 --> 11:00.400
who have built the Catholic
school system in this country,

11:00.493 --> 11:02.280
brick by brick.

11:02.370 --> 11:05.204
Your little one is so
lovely, by the way.

11:05.290 --> 11:07.703
May I ask how old?

11:07.792 --> 11:08.999
Cathleen is 12.

11:10.295 --> 11:13.163
Look, we appreciate
your coming by,

11:13.256 --> 11:16.624
but the truth is, we're
not all that religious.

11:17.051 --> 11:19.589
I mean, we go to church when
we can, like everybody else.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.137
But my husband, Cathleen's father,

11:22.223 --> 11:25.682
he left us a while back, so
it's just me taking care of us.

11:25.768 --> 11:28.511
Sorry to hear that, Mrs Harris.

11:28.605 --> 11:30.437
God cherishes your strength.

11:30.523 --> 11:32.480
But one thing you should know,

11:32.567 --> 11:34.900
our doors are open to everyone,

11:34.986 --> 11:37.569
practising, non-practising alike.

11:37.655 --> 11:42.070
Our first priority is just to
provide an exceptional education.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.704
Well, how much does
it cost? I don't

11:45.705 --> 11:47.280
know if we can afford this school.

11:47.373 --> 11:49.080
Well, that's just it.

11:49.167 --> 11:52.001
Right now, we're offering
full scholarships

11:52.587 --> 11:54.249
on a first-come basis.

11:54.339 --> 11:56.251
Silence, girls.

11:56.341 --> 11:57.832
Silence.

11:59.886 --> 12:02.549
How many in this room
were baptised Catholic?

12:04.682 --> 12:06.822
Don't worry, this
is not a judgement

12:06.823 --> 12:08.847
on anybody's background or belief.

12:08.937 --> 12:12.851
No, the reason I ask the question

12:12.941 --> 12:16.309
is because I wonder
if any of you know

12:16.402 --> 12:19.941
what the difference is between
the Catholic religion

12:20.031 --> 12:21.567
and all the other religions.

12:21.658 --> 12:25.868
Say like, the Protestants,
the Baptists, the Jews?

12:27.872 --> 12:29.204
Love

12:30.583 --> 12:34.167
and sacrifice.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.917
Love and sacrifice.

12:38.925 --> 12:42.293
Because if there's one
thing I know for certain,

12:42.387 --> 12:45.676
there can be no love

12:45.765 --> 12:48.178
without sacrifice.

12:57.860 --> 12:59.271
Hi, there.

12:59.362 --> 13:01.604
How come you're sitting all alone?

13:01.698 --> 13:04.281
You don't wanna join the others?

13:06.494 --> 13:08.702
They're all talking
about their boyfriends.

13:10.331 --> 13:12.288
I don't have a boyfriend.

13:12.375 --> 13:13.741
Oh, no?

13:14.877 --> 13:16.038
Me, neither.

13:16.129 --> 13:18.041
I'm told they're overrated.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.589
Mind if I join you?

13:23.094 --> 13:26.553
I'm Sister Margaret, by the
way. You're Cathleen, right?

13:27.265 --> 13:30.429
I haven't had you in my class
yet, but I've noticed you

13:30.518 --> 13:32.555
because you're shy, like me.

13:32.645 --> 13:37.185
You seem to like to be by
yourself a lot, to think a lot?

13:37.275 --> 13:39.016
I guess so.

13:39.110 --> 13:42.103
I like to be by myself
and think a lot, too.

13:42.822 --> 13:43.822
You do?

13:44.449 --> 13:46.190
What do you like to think about?

13:46.284 --> 13:48.776
Mostly about God.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.290
Can I show you something?

13:57.295 --> 13:59.252
You see that light in there?

14:00.089 --> 14:02.126
That's His light.

14:02.759 --> 14:07.550
And the statue to the side, the
Saviour, of course, Jesus Christ.

14:09.349 --> 14:11.341
Here, you wanna sit
down for a sec?

14:17.482 --> 14:18.689
Go ahead.

14:22.945 --> 14:25.779
Just because someone
likes to be alone

14:25.865 --> 14:28.733
doesn't mean they don't
still crave intimacy.

14:31.162 --> 14:35.497
You really think God
and Jesus are real?

14:35.583 --> 14:38.917
Of course I do. I more than do.

14:39.003 --> 14:41.336
Because I'm married
to them, silly.

14:42.590 --> 14:45.958
Didn't you know? All nuns
are brides of Christ.

14:47.428 --> 14:48.760
But why?

14:48.846 --> 14:51.680
I bet you could have married
anyone you wanted to.

14:53.017 --> 14:56.681
Well, I'm not so sure about that.

14:58.022 --> 14:59.263
And either way,

14:59.357 --> 15:01.648
I doubt any other
relationship would

15:01.649 --> 15:03.567
have been quite as fulfilling.

15:06.030 --> 15:08.488
I gotta go. I've got class.

15:15.039 --> 15:16.200
Are you coming?

15:16.290 --> 15:19.030
I think I'll stay
for a little while,

15:19.031 --> 15:21.410
if that's okay with you, Sister.

15:22.255 --> 15:23.541
Of course.

15:49.365 --> 15:50.822
Good night, Cathleen.

15:50.908 --> 15:52.490
Good night, Miss Williams.

16:05.798 --> 16:06.834
Hi.

16:11.679 --> 16:13.215
Who is he?

16:15.516 --> 16:18.475
He's just a friend
of mine, that's all.

16:18.561 --> 16:19.802
Another one?

16:22.607 --> 16:25.145
What are you doing
up so early, anyway?

16:25.234 --> 16:27.977
I set my alarm so I can
go to Mass before school.

16:30.072 --> 16:31.072
Okay.

16:33.493 --> 16:34.779
You need a ride?

16:34.869 --> 16:36.576
That's okay.

16:40.917 --> 16:42.124
Hey, Cathleen?

16:44.587 --> 16:49.423
You're not getting too into God
and all that stuff, are you?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.006
What do you mean?

16:53.095 --> 16:57.089
I just mean there's more to life
than God and church and praying.

18:04.166 --> 18:05.998
You're serious, Cathleen?

18:08.462 --> 18:12.672
I honestly didn't even realise
you'd been considering this.

18:12.758 --> 18:15.091
I want to give my life to God.

18:16.178 --> 18:18.386
You're such a passionate girl.

18:18.472 --> 18:21.135
You remind me of
myself at your age.

18:21.225 --> 18:23.638
I think you're making
the right decision.

18:23.728 --> 18:26.391
A nun? What are you talking about?

18:26.480 --> 18:28.392
That's just fucking
crazy, Cathleen.

18:28.482 --> 18:29.563
I knew you wouldn't understand,

18:29.650 --> 18:31.117
but you don't have to
understand. I didn't...

18:31.193 --> 18:32.309
It's not that I don't understand,

18:32.403 --> 18:35.237
it's just that it's the
stupidest idea I've ever heard.

18:35.323 --> 18:37.110
You throw your life
away in some convent...

18:37.199 --> 18:38.406
But I'm not throwing my life away.

18:38.492 --> 18:39.903
I don't know how you
can even say that...

18:39.994 --> 18:41.361
You're absolutely
throwing your life away.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.195
Well, I don't get it.

18:43.289 --> 18:44.325
Do you think I wanted this?

18:44.415 --> 18:45.872
Do you think I wanted
to be a single mother?

18:45.958 --> 18:47.790
But it's not about that. It
has nothing to do with you.

18:47.877 --> 18:48.877
Then what is it?

18:48.961 --> 18:51.328
- I'm in love, Mum.
- You're in love with who?

18:53.049 --> 18:54.631
What?

18:57.845 --> 18:59.131
God?

19:00.056 --> 19:03.049
Oh, my God, that's crazy.
That is fucking crazy.

19:03.142 --> 19:06.306
That doesn't even make
sense, "in love with God."

19:07.563 --> 19:09.600
I don't know how to explain this,

19:11.025 --> 19:12.937
but I was called, and
I'm gonna become a nun.

19:13.027 --> 19:14.438
And there's really
nothing that you can say

19:14.528 --> 19:16.110
that's gonna make
me change my mind.

19:19.450 --> 19:20.941
Cathleen.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.320
You're a 17-year-old girl.

19:26.415 --> 19:28.498
You don't know anything
about religion.

19:29.669 --> 19:32.878
And you sure as hell don't
know anything about love.

19:47.311 --> 19:48.768
Where are you?

19:51.982 --> 19:53.564
It's not right.

19:56.112 --> 19:57.819
It's not fair.

19:59.365 --> 20:01.527
Someone gives you
their whole life...

20:03.828 --> 20:05.239
Where are you?

20:37.653 --> 20:39.315
Good afternoon, all of you.

20:39.405 --> 20:42.773
My name is Reverend
Mother Marie St Clair.

20:42.867 --> 20:45.402
You can call me
"Reverend Mother," or

20:45.403 --> 20:47.737
simply "Mother," if you prefer it.

20:48.497 --> 20:51.035
I am the Mother
Superior, or Abbess

20:51.125 --> 20:55.369
of this particular order of
Sisters of Beloved Rose.

20:56.046 --> 20:59.960
I myself have been a Rose
for nearly 40 years.

21:00.050 --> 21:03.134
Meaning, some 40 years ago,

21:03.220 --> 21:05.462
I first came through those
gates as a postulant,

21:05.556 --> 21:07.218
same as all of you.

21:07.892 --> 21:11.385
And now, 40 years later,

21:11.479 --> 21:15.268
I have not once set foot
outside those gates.

21:16.233 --> 21:19.067
So, as far as all of
you are concerned,

21:19.153 --> 21:21.941
you might consider me like the
voice of God around here.

21:22.823 --> 21:24.985
Meaning, since unfortunately

21:25.075 --> 21:28.159
God can't be here to run
this convent Himself,

21:28.245 --> 21:32.489
my voice will serve as
a stand-in for His.

21:32.583 --> 21:36.076
And you can expect that
whenever you hear me speak,

21:36.170 --> 21:39.038
it is on behalf of His wishes.

21:40.007 --> 21:41.339
And over the next two years,

21:41.425 --> 21:45.260
I personally will be separating
the wheat from the chaff,

21:45.679 --> 21:49.389
determining which of
you actually belong,

21:49.475 --> 21:50.841
as opposed to which of you

21:50.935 --> 21:54.645
are simply victims of a
childish imagination.

21:55.147 --> 22:00.438
Because in this monastery,
God is not a fantasy to us.

22:01.111 --> 22:04.900
Not a fantasy, not a daydream,

22:04.990 --> 22:07.653
and certainly not your
invisible best friend.

22:08.869 --> 22:12.533
To the contrary, God
is work. Hard work.

22:12.623 --> 22:16.958
The work of a very
special kind of love,

22:17.044 --> 22:18.831
which you'll all be trained in.

22:19.755 --> 22:23.169
You'll be spending the next
six months as postulants.

22:24.260 --> 22:26.843
After that, and for those
of you who make it,

22:26.929 --> 22:31.173
you'll take your very first
vows and enter the novitiate.

22:31.267 --> 22:35.136
And as a rule, we make it a point
to never discuss the novitiate

22:35.229 --> 22:37.846
until we've been
through it ourselves.

22:37.940 --> 22:42.105
So for now, you'll
just have to wait.

22:42.778 --> 22:46.237
Finally, I'd like to
talk about silence.

22:46.824 --> 22:49.658
We observe two kinds
of silence here,

22:49.743 --> 22:53.783
regular silence and grand silence.

22:53.873 --> 22:55.284
During regular silence,

22:55.374 --> 22:58.742
if you feel you have the need
to speak, it's permissible.

22:58.836 --> 23:01.704
But when you hear that
bell at 9:00 at night,

23:01.797 --> 23:04.790
signifying the beginning
of grand silence,

23:04.884 --> 23:09.299
that means you don't talk.

23:10.306 --> 23:11.672
Any questions?

23:13.767 --> 23:16.601
Put your hand down, Sister.
Postulants don't have questions.

23:16.687 --> 23:18.770
And you are free to go home.

24:47.903 --> 24:49.269
Good afternoon, Mother.
Praise the Lord.

24:49.363 --> 24:50.729
Now and forever. God bless.

24:51.740 --> 24:54.608
- Praise the Lord.
- Now and forever. God bless.

24:55.077 --> 24:56.659
Good afternoon, Mother.
Praise the Lord.

24:56.745 --> 24:58.702
Now and forever.
God bless, Sister.

25:05.671 --> 25:09.631
Totally love Him, who gave
Himself totally for your love.

25:10.551 --> 25:13.794
He, Christ, is the splendour
of eternal glory,

25:13.887 --> 25:17.972
the brightness of eternal light
and the mirror without cloud.

25:25.065 --> 25:27.728
I haven't had the chance to
formally introduce myself yet.

25:27.818 --> 25:29.650
I'm Sister Mary Grace.

25:29.737 --> 25:32.480
I will be your postulant mistress
for the next six months,

25:32.573 --> 25:35.156
perhaps your novice
mistress after that.

25:35.242 --> 25:37.404
This is Sister Anne.

25:38.078 --> 25:40.286
Sister Catherine, Kate.

25:40.372 --> 25:43.740
Both professed nuns. Both
just took their final vows.

25:43.834 --> 25:45.621
We're very proud of them.

25:45.711 --> 25:48.200
Now, it is our job
to help guide you as

25:48.201 --> 25:50.502
you try to adapt to
our way of life.

25:50.591 --> 25:54.005
I'm sure at the beginning,
it will feel very different.

25:54.094 --> 25:55.756
That's normal.

25:55.846 --> 26:00.557
I remember when I first came here,
everything seemed so strange.

26:00.642 --> 26:03.510
I didn't know if I'd ever
truly make it as a nun.

26:03.604 --> 26:05.561
Please don't worry about that.

26:05.647 --> 26:07.309
I'm sure you all will be great.

26:08.192 --> 26:11.026
Now, we should probably
go over the schedule.

26:11.695 --> 26:15.530
Postulants usually have the
same schedule every single day.

26:15.616 --> 26:18.984
The most important thing to
pay attention to is the bell.

26:19.078 --> 26:21.946
Pretty much everything we
do here, all day long,

26:22.039 --> 26:23.405
all comes down to the bell.

26:27.211 --> 26:31.080
The first bell you'll hear each
morning is the 5:00 am bell.

26:32.549 --> 26:34.131
That bell lets everyone know

26:34.218 --> 26:37.427
it's time to wake up, get
ready for morning Mass.

26:47.314 --> 26:50.022
Mass begins once
Father Luca arrives.

26:50.109 --> 26:53.318
Father Luca always keeps his
back to us the whole time,

26:53.403 --> 26:56.111
and he always reads
the liturgy in Latin.

26:56.198 --> 26:57.939
Sometimes it's hard to keep up.

26:59.827 --> 27:01.068
After daily chores,

27:01.161 --> 27:03.403
you'll hear the third
bell of the morning.

27:03.497 --> 27:06.581
That lets us know that
grand silence is over.

27:07.501 --> 27:09.868
Good afternoon, Mother.
Praise the Lord.

27:11.964 --> 27:13.546
Now and forever. God bless.

27:13.632 --> 27:16.045
Good afternoon, Mother.
Praise the Lord.

27:17.761 --> 27:21.880
As you probably noticed, all our
meals begin with a reading.

27:21.974 --> 27:23.715
Even though it's
after grand silence,

27:23.809 --> 27:27.177
we should all try and remain
as quiet as possible.

27:28.063 --> 27:29.770
Sometimes you might see
some of the novices

27:29.857 --> 27:32.895
doing their own penances
in the refectory.

27:32.985 --> 27:36.569
Probably best to just ignore it
until you're novices yourselves.

27:39.658 --> 27:43.868
Every day after the 3:00 pm bell,
we'll have our lessons together.

27:43.954 --> 27:47.948
As you probably remember, Reverend
Mother made it absolutely clear

27:48.041 --> 27:51.534
that we are not to speak
during grand silence,

27:51.628 --> 27:54.211
so let's practise a little
bit of sign language.

27:54.298 --> 27:56.085
Slowly, that is, "What...

27:59.011 --> 28:00.011
"Job...

28:03.807 --> 28:05.093
"Right now?"

28:39.801 --> 28:40.882
Sorry to interrupt, Mother,

28:40.969 --> 28:44.053
but you just got another
package from the Archdiocese.

28:44.139 --> 28:45.139
What?

28:59.071 --> 29:01.404
They can't be serious.

29:03.492 --> 29:05.074
Thank you, Sister.

29:09.998 --> 29:12.160
What are they asking of us?

29:18.799 --> 29:24.136
My mother always said at least
one child should be sacrificed.

29:24.221 --> 29:26.884
And even though I come
from a big family,

29:26.974 --> 29:29.637
I'm the only girl
with five brothers,

29:29.726 --> 29:35.063
so I guess it was pretty obvious
who was going to become a nun.

29:35.691 --> 29:38.559
Honestly, though, I'm
really happy to be here.

29:38.652 --> 29:42.236
And I know that it's
supposed to be so hard,

29:42.322 --> 29:46.282
but I really can't wait
until we get to novitiate

29:46.368 --> 29:48.735
and we get to wear
those white veils.

29:50.289 --> 29:51.450
Who wants to go next?

29:54.960 --> 29:58.499
Well, as for me, I
have two cousins,

29:58.588 --> 30:02.923
an aunt and one older sister
who joined the Sisterhood.

30:03.010 --> 30:07.254
So, I guess, in a way,
it's kind of in my blood.

30:07.973 --> 30:11.592
And who knows, maybe one day I'll
die young and become a saint.

30:14.271 --> 30:15.432
Thank you, Sister Emily.

30:17.941 --> 30:22.060
Sister Cathleen, did you always
know that you wanted to be a nun?

30:24.489 --> 30:27.197
No, actually, I wasn't
raised in the Church, so...

30:27.284 --> 30:30.277
What do you mean, you weren't
raised in the Church?

30:30.370 --> 30:31.486
Aren't you Catholic?

30:31.580 --> 30:35.950
I guess I'm not Catholic in the
same way that you guys are.

30:36.043 --> 30:37.784
Well, what are you
even doing here, then?

30:37.878 --> 30:39.585
I mean, is this even allowed?

30:39.671 --> 30:41.913
Sister Candace, please. Ladies.

30:43.467 --> 30:44.708
I went to Catholic school.

30:45.135 --> 30:46.842
That's where I learned
about the Sisters.

30:46.928 --> 30:51.218
I just thought it seemed like
the most beautiful idea,

30:52.184 --> 30:55.348
to be able to spend my
entire life devoted to love.

30:57.814 --> 30:59.430
Tell me about the new postulants.

30:59.524 --> 31:01.436
I'm so impressed with
them as a group.

31:01.526 --> 31:04.485
They're full of energy
and enthusiasm,

31:04.571 --> 31:06.201
really passionate
about finding their

31:06.202 --> 31:07.530
own relationships with Christ.

31:14.456 --> 31:15.788
What is this you're reading?

31:15.874 --> 31:20.790
This is something to do
with this Vatican II.

31:22.214 --> 31:23.750
Vatican what?

31:26.718 --> 31:28.209
From what I can make out,

31:28.303 --> 31:30.545
our Pope has suddenly
got it into his head

31:30.639 --> 31:33.677
to turn himself into
some sort of reformer.

31:33.767 --> 31:35.599
Meaning what, exactly?

31:35.685 --> 31:38.428
Meaning he's organised some
ridiculous new council in Rome

31:38.522 --> 31:41.105
to speak about changes
to the Church.

31:41.191 --> 31:43.524
Well, that's a good
thing, isn't it?

31:44.277 --> 31:47.395
The Church hasn't reviewed its
practises in over 100 years.

31:47.489 --> 31:48.489
Perhaps change is...

31:48.573 --> 31:50.064
You think the Church
is in need of change?

31:51.034 --> 31:53.117
Are you questioning me?

31:53.203 --> 31:55.866
I happen to think the Church
is perfect the way it is.

31:55.956 --> 31:58.323
Well, what reforms are
they talking about?

31:58.417 --> 32:00.784
- Can I see?
- It's not important.

32:01.420 --> 32:03.036
This will all blow over very soon.

32:03.130 --> 32:05.543
It's nothing to concern
yourself with.

32:05.632 --> 32:08.090
Pay attention. I'm going
to show you how we walk.

32:08.176 --> 32:10.634
It's called "custody of the eyes."

32:10.720 --> 32:13.633
You put your hands in
your sleeve like this.

32:13.723 --> 32:17.512
Always go slowly, gracefully,
never in a hurry.

32:17.602 --> 32:20.515
And most important is you
keep your eyes down.

32:20.605 --> 32:21.937
Always make sure you're looking

32:22.023 --> 32:24.106
straight ahead at the
floor in front of you.

32:24.192 --> 32:25.273
Why?

32:25.360 --> 32:26.567
Excuse me?

32:27.320 --> 32:28.856
Why do we have to walk like that?

32:28.947 --> 32:31.314
I mean, what if we can't
see where we're going?

32:33.660 --> 32:35.367
Not that it's your place
to question anything,

32:35.454 --> 32:36.911
but it's a part of our discipline.

32:36.997 --> 32:38.238
We keep our eyes down

32:38.331 --> 32:40.288
so we don't allow in
any extra stimulation

32:40.375 --> 32:42.162
that might distract
us from our Lord.

32:44.087 --> 32:45.953
Something funny, Sisters?

32:46.548 --> 32:47.664
You two, come here.

32:48.508 --> 32:49.508
Come on.

32:52.053 --> 32:53.669
Stand face-to-face.

32:55.348 --> 32:57.840
Now, both of you look at
each other in the eyes.

33:15.619 --> 33:19.329
- What just happened?
- I started thinking about her.

33:20.999 --> 33:23.537
Yeah, I started thinking
about her, too.

33:23.627 --> 33:26.461
Exactly. We're not supposed
to think about each other.

33:26.546 --> 33:30.415
Because we're not here for each
other, we are here only for God.

33:31.176 --> 33:32.383
Move on, Sisters.

33:36.932 --> 33:38.548
I love you, God.

33:47.234 --> 33:48.975
Thank you for letting me be here.

33:51.238 --> 33:53.571
Thank you for letting
me love you like this.

33:57.661 --> 34:00.404
Thank you for letting me
feel you so close to me.

34:01.039 --> 34:02.405
Thank you.

34:07.921 --> 34:09.456
I love you, God.

34:13.051 --> 34:14.632
I love you so much.

34:17.013 --> 34:21.098
This is the first time I've
seen you in your outfit.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.219
Yeah.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.099
Do you like it?

34:26.188 --> 34:28.897
- You look like a real nun.
- Thanks.

34:29.818 --> 34:32.481
I'm not a real nun
yet. Not yet, but...

34:34.114 --> 34:35.480
What is with this thing?

34:35.574 --> 34:38.987
This is terrible.
It's like prison.

34:39.077 --> 34:41.284
Yeah, it's just the
way they do it.

34:41.371 --> 34:44.580
It's like a symbol
of our enclosure.

34:44.666 --> 34:46.123
What the...

34:47.960 --> 34:49.452
What does that mean?

34:51.255 --> 34:52.417
It's nothing.

34:54.634 --> 34:56.466
So, how are you?

34:57.137 --> 35:00.676
Are you... You like it
here? Are you happy?

35:00.765 --> 35:02.131
Yeah.

35:02.809 --> 35:04.300
Yeah, I am.

35:06.062 --> 35:11.353
I don't know how to describe it,
but it feels like I belong here.

35:13.987 --> 35:16.342
I guess that means
you plan on staying,

35:16.343 --> 35:18.402
and you plan on taking those vows.

35:18.491 --> 35:20.574
What do they call
it, the "novanate"?

35:20.660 --> 35:23.403
- Novitiate.
- "Novitiate." Nova-something?

35:25.373 --> 35:27.349
Yeah, it's just a temporary vow

35:27.350 --> 35:29.708
that we take for a
year and a half.

35:29.794 --> 35:32.002
And we find out

35:32.088 --> 35:36.549
if we're ready to
marry God forever.

35:39.679 --> 35:42.968
I'm pretty sure I'm going
to be here my whole life.

35:44.601 --> 35:48.595
Jesus Christ, Cathleen, what
the hell did I do wrong?

35:55.195 --> 35:56.195
How...

35:57.656 --> 35:58.817
How have you been?

36:01.618 --> 36:02.904
Well, I'm just fine.

36:03.870 --> 36:07.034
I picked up a few more shifts
at work, keeping myself busy.

36:07.123 --> 36:09.786
I don't really know
what to do with myself.

36:10.794 --> 36:15.539
Because I most... I... I
mostly just miss you so much.

36:16.966 --> 36:20.209
How about Dad? How's Dad?

36:20.303 --> 36:21.934
Have you heard anything from Dad?

36:21.935 --> 36:22.935
Your father? No.

36:23.515 --> 36:27.725
Your grandma did call and said
he'd been sick or something.

36:27.811 --> 36:29.803
That's probably why you
haven't heard from him.

36:29.896 --> 36:31.128
But do you want me
to track him down?

36:31.129 --> 36:32.296
I'm sure he'd love
to come see you.

36:32.357 --> 36:36.271
That's okay, don't bother.
I'll pray for him.

36:37.320 --> 36:38.982
It's fine.

36:39.948 --> 36:42.031
But it's like a... It's
a really busy day here.

36:42.117 --> 36:44.200
I should get going.

36:44.285 --> 36:48.120
What? No. We have
ten more minutes.

36:48.206 --> 36:50.620
I know, but I just
have a lot of work.

36:50.621 --> 36:51.916
What are you doing?

36:52.001 --> 36:53.993
Maybe we can spend more time
together next time, though.

36:54.087 --> 36:58.582
Okay. Well, can you just wait?
Wait, wait, wait. Wait one second?

37:01.469 --> 37:04.678
Maybe I could just touch
your hand for a second.

37:07.475 --> 37:09.182
- Just for a second.
- Yeah...

37:09.811 --> 37:11.848
We're really not supposed to
touch like that, Mum, so...

37:11.938 --> 37:13.804
- Okay.
- I gotta go.

37:14.607 --> 37:17.395
Okay. Cathleen, I love you.

37:18.236 --> 37:19.602
Thank you for coming.

37:21.614 --> 37:22.821
Oh, God.

37:36.463 --> 37:40.958
I guess I just didn't really know
it was going to be like this.

37:41.050 --> 37:42.131
Like what?

37:42.218 --> 37:44.122
That we'll be spending our whole

37:44.123 --> 37:46.383
entire lives here
and never leaving.

37:46.473 --> 37:49.011
We won't even be able to go
to our own parents' funerals.

37:49.100 --> 37:51.030
Who cares? They'll
be dead, anyway.

37:51.031 --> 37:52.639
It's not like they'll notice.

37:53.730 --> 37:58.646
Besides, don't you think knowing
God knows we're here for Him,

37:58.735 --> 38:01.218
knowing we are so
much more special

38:01.219 --> 38:03.150
to Him than anybody else...

38:03.823 --> 38:06.190
Don't you think that
makes it all worth it?

38:08.661 --> 38:10.573
Yeah, I guess.

38:10.663 --> 38:13.201
Well, why did you come here, then?

38:14.584 --> 38:15.950
Audrey Hepburn.

38:18.087 --> 38:19.749
What are you talking about?

38:20.340 --> 38:21.797
Audrey Hepburn.

38:22.926 --> 38:25.669
I wanted to be a nun

38:25.762 --> 38:31.554
because I saw A Nun's Story,
and she's Sister Gabrielle.

38:32.352 --> 38:33.593
And I just thought

38:33.686 --> 38:38.727
she was so holy and
beautiful and perfect.

38:41.528 --> 38:44.487
I wanted to be like
her. Don't laugh at me.

38:44.572 --> 38:47.189
That's not very holy.

38:48.284 --> 38:49.650
I won't tell anybody.

38:50.370 --> 38:52.077
This was a mistake.

38:53.706 --> 38:55.493
I was too young for it.

39:00.296 --> 39:03.084
I didn't ever mean
to disappoint you.

39:08.429 --> 39:11.092
I just don't know if
I feel it, you know?

39:13.309 --> 39:14.390
Feel what?

39:17.730 --> 39:21.394
My relationship with Him.

39:22.569 --> 39:24.856
Whatever we're supposed to feel.

39:28.950 --> 39:33.365
I can't tell if I'm
communicating with Him,

39:33.955 --> 39:37.665
and it's really Him or if
it's just all in my head.

39:41.212 --> 39:45.582
Reverend Mother says we can't fake

39:45.675 --> 39:47.507
our relationship with Him.

39:48.720 --> 39:50.461
Because if...

39:50.555 --> 39:55.095
Even if nobody else knows, He'll
know and He'll shun us for it.

39:57.353 --> 40:01.097
But I'm just worried,
what if I'm faking it,

40:01.691 --> 40:03.808
and I don't even realise?

41:29.570 --> 41:32.028
No, I have them right
here in front of me. I...

41:38.621 --> 41:41.034
It's not that I wasn't
going to respond. I...

41:43.126 --> 41:45.368
Of course I understand
the historic...

41:50.341 --> 41:52.048
And also with you.

42:22.457 --> 42:23.457
Good morning, Reverend Mother.

42:23.541 --> 42:25.032
- Praise the Lord.
- Now and forever.

42:25.960 --> 42:27.826
Did you just speak?

42:29.213 --> 42:31.125
Did I just hear you speak?

42:36.304 --> 42:39.263
What's your name?

42:41.517 --> 42:42.633
I'm Sister Sissy.

42:42.727 --> 42:44.138
Sister Sissy?

42:45.354 --> 42:47.767
Well, Sister Sissy...

42:49.442 --> 42:52.105
Why don't you tell me what
you've been doing lately,

42:52.195 --> 42:55.063
besides getting fat,
being late for Mass,

42:55.823 --> 42:58.486
and talking during grand silence.

43:02.830 --> 43:06.790
I didn't realise it was
still grand silence.

43:08.044 --> 43:11.082
Well, because they told us to
count the bells before noon.

43:11.172 --> 43:12.172
And I counted...

43:12.256 --> 43:14.714
Do you not understand
what "silence" means?

43:15.468 --> 43:17.676
Was it not explained
to you properly?

43:20.640 --> 43:23.508
During grand silence,
you are silent.

43:24.102 --> 43:26.936
And silence means you don't talk.

43:27.021 --> 43:28.762
You shut your mouth.

43:30.817 --> 43:34.527
But, Reverend Mother,
you're talking.

43:34.612 --> 43:37.320
That is because I am reprimanding
you right now, Jenny.

43:37.406 --> 43:40.490
- I am reprimanding you.
- It's "Sissy."

43:44.372 --> 43:45.954
I don't care in the least.

43:46.040 --> 43:47.906
I want you to get down
on your hands and knees

43:48.000 --> 43:49.000
and crawl all the way here.

43:49.085 --> 43:52.499
Say as many Hail Marys as you
can, from here to there.

43:53.005 --> 43:54.621
Right now.

43:55.675 --> 43:57.837
On your hands and knees, Sister.

44:01.848 --> 44:03.965
Hail... Hail Mary...

44:04.183 --> 44:05.890
Are you talking?

44:06.102 --> 44:08.936
Do I still hear you talking?

44:15.194 --> 44:17.106
Silence.

44:56.110 --> 44:58.022
I didn't have any clue.

45:00.406 --> 45:02.489
Sorry. I didn't realise
anybody was here.

45:02.575 --> 45:03.575
No, no, it's okay.

45:05.494 --> 45:06.860
Come here.

45:07.121 --> 45:09.078
Come here. I'd like
to talk to you.

45:19.675 --> 45:22.133
- How are you, Sister Cathleen?
- Good.

45:23.721 --> 45:24.962
Thank you.

45:26.140 --> 45:28.223
And the other girls?

45:28.309 --> 45:30.892
Are they still upset about
Sister Sissy being sent home?

45:32.438 --> 45:35.055
Everybody mostly understands.

45:36.108 --> 45:38.350
We all miss her. I
miss her, but...

45:38.694 --> 45:40.026
Of course.

45:41.656 --> 45:44.023
Do you often come here
to pray by yourself?

45:44.367 --> 45:45.949
Sometimes.

45:46.994 --> 45:49.281
Especially now that our
first vows are coming up.

45:49.664 --> 45:53.624
I just wanted to spend some extra
time communicating with Him,

45:53.709 --> 45:58.079
and make sure He's okay
with me becoming a novice.

45:59.298 --> 46:01.631
I'm pretty sure He's okay with it.

46:03.135 --> 46:05.593
I think you're gonna
be a great nun.

46:05.680 --> 46:07.216
Thank you, Sister.

46:19.986 --> 46:22.148
Just do me a favour, okay?

46:23.531 --> 46:26.444
Please make sure this
is what you want.

46:28.661 --> 46:30.573
Do you understand what I'm saying?

46:33.833 --> 46:35.165
Okay.

46:36.669 --> 46:39.412
Lord, please forgive me, I
haven't done well today.

46:41.507 --> 46:43.749
I didn't focus enough on
my prayers this morning,

46:43.843 --> 46:45.129
and I rushed to Mass

46:46.554 --> 46:48.887
because I just wanted
to be with my friends.

46:51.309 --> 46:53.676
And I'm sorry,
sometimes I feel like

46:53.894 --> 46:56.682
I pay more attention to
my friends than I do you.

46:58.649 --> 47:00.481
And I just pray that
you censure my heart,

47:01.610 --> 47:04.853
and you centre my thoughts
and my mind only on you.

47:04.947 --> 47:07.610
You shall speak to him

47:07.700 --> 47:11.193
And put the words in his mouth

47:11.287 --> 47:14.405
And I will be with your mouth

